ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Greetings from London. I propose we coordinate our opening moves to mutual advantage. I intend to move F EDI to NTH and F LON to ENG, positioning myself for Belgium. I have no designs on Denmark or Holland - those are yours to take. In return, I ask that you keep your fleet in KIE and not contest the North Sea. A strong Anglo-German understanding from the start benefits us both against France and Russia. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "My friend in Paris - let us establish an understanding from the outset. I have no intention of moving against Brest or your Atlantic coast. My focus is on the North Sea and Scandinavia. I propose we respect each other's spheres: the Channel remains neutral between us, and we both expand elsewhere. I'd welcome your thoughts on coordinating against Germany if they prove aggressive. What are your opening intentions?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Greetings from London. Britain and Russia have complementary interests - we need not clash. I intend to expand into Scandinavia via the North Sea, and I'd welcome an understanding that Norway falls to me while Sweden and the Baltic remain your domain. In return, I can support your interests diplomatically against common threats. What are your plans for the north?"}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Greetings from Constantinople. I propose we establish a clear understanding early: I have no interest in Sevastopol or the Black Sea if you have no interest in the Balkans. My fleet in Ankara will move to the Black Sea only if you threaten my position - otherwise I intend to push west into Bulgaria and Greece. I suggest you focus your southern fleet on Rumania while I take Bulgaria. We can divide the Balkans peacefully and both grow stronger against Austria. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, let us speak plainly. I intend to move into Bulgaria this spring - it is the natural Turkish sphere. I have no designs on Serbia or Rumania, which I leave to you. In return, I ask that you keep your fleet in Trieste and not contest the Aegean. A Turkish-Austrian understanding in the Balkans benefits us both against Russian expansion southward. Can we agree on a division: Bulgaria and Greece for Turkey, Serbia and Rumania for Austria?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I reach out as a potential partner in the Mediterranean. My ambitions lie primarily in the Balkans and Black Sea - I have no quarrel with you in the Ionian or Adriatic. However, I note Austria sits between us both. If you find yourself in conflict with Vienna, know that Turkey can apply pressure from the east. For now, let us simply agree to non-interference in each other's immediate expansion zones. I move toward Bulgaria; you move toward Tunis. Agreed?"}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Comrade, let us speak plainly. We both have interests in the Balkans and Black Sea region, but conflict between us serves only our enemies. I propose a non-aggression pact: I will move F SEV to RUM this spring, leaving the Black Sea and Armenia untouched. In return, I ask that you keep your fleet in ANK and not contest the Black Sea. Romania is mine; Bulgaria and the Aegean are yours. A strong Russia and Turkey together can dominate the east. Agree?'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I wish to establish friendly relations from the outset. I have no designs on Galicia or your home centers - my expansion is directed toward Romania and Scandinavia. I propose we both stay out of Galicia this spring to avoid any misunderstanding. In return, I will not move A WAR into GAL. Let us focus our energies outward rather than against each other. A stable eastern front benefits us both.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I propose a straightforward arrangement for the north: I will take Norway via F STP/SC, and you take Sweden via the Baltic. We need not compete in Scandinavia if we coordinate. I have no interest in Prussia or Silesia this year - my army in Warsaw moves south toward Romania. Let us establish a working relationship and avoid unnecessary friction on our shared border.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, let us establish a firm understanding from the outset. Germany has no designs on Vienna or your Balkan territories - our expansion lies to the north and west. I propose we coordinate: I will move into Silesia and push toward Denmark and Holland, while you secure the Balkans. A strong Austria-Germany axis will dominate Central Europe. I ask only that you keep your armies away from Bohemia and Tyrolia - those are buffer zones I need clear. In return, I will not interfere with your moves into Serbia, Rumania, or Greece. Do we have an understanding?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, Germany seeks peaceful relations in the east - for now. I have no intention of moving into Warsaw or threatening your western frontier this year. My focus is entirely on Denmark, Holland, and the North Sea. I propose a non-aggression pact: you stay out of Prussia and Silesia, I stay out of your territories. We can both expand freely in our natural directions - you toward the Balkans and Turkey, me toward the west. A conflict between us only benefits England and France. Let us be pragmatic.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I want to be direct with you: Germany's fleet is moving to Denmark this spring, and my army will secure Holland. These are natural German interests. I have no desire for conflict with Britain - the sea is yours, the continent is mine. I propose we respect each other's spheres: you dominate the Atlantic and focus on France if you wish, while I consolidate Central Europe. A Anglo-German understanding benefits us both enormously. France is the common threat to both our ambitions - consider that carefully."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Greetings from Vienna. I propose we establish a clear understanding from the outset: I have no designs on Venice, and I trust you have no designs on Trieste. Let us both focus our energies outward - I intend to move on Serbia and Romania, while you push south and west. A non-aggression pact between us frees both our hands considerably. I'd suggest F TRI moves to ADR to support your southern ambitions, while you keep A VEN out of TYR. Shall we formalize this arrangement?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Fellow power of the east - I believe we share a common interest in keeping Russia contained. I intend to push into the Balkans (Serbia, Romania) and would welcome coordination with you on the Black Sea region. If you move into Bulgaria, we can divide the Balkans cleanly: Bulgaria and Greece to you, Serbia and Romania to me. Russia is the long-term threat to us both. Let us discuss how we might cooperate against them.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'I write in the spirit of good neighborly relations. Austria has no aggressive intentions toward Russia at this stage - I am focused on the neutral Balkan territories. I propose we respect a Galicia buffer: neither of us moves armies into Galicia this turn, keeping the peace between our nations. I believe we can coexist profitably while both expanding into neutral territories. What are your thoughts?'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Greetings from Rome. I propose we establish a clear understanding from the start: I have no designs on Trieste, and I hope you have none on Venice. Italy's natural expansion lies south and east - toward Tunis, Greece, and the Balkans beyond. I suggest we coordinate: I will move F NAP to ION and A VEN to TRI... wait, let me be direct - I will NOT move on Trieste this turn. I propose A VEN moves to TYR to support your western flank against Germany if needed, while I focus south. In return, I ask that F TRI stays out of ADR and we discuss a joint approach to the Balkans. What say you?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Sultan, let us speak plainly. Both Italy and Turkey stand to gain enormously in the Mediterranean and Balkans, but only if we avoid conflict with each other. I intend to move my fleet toward Tunis this season - I have no immediate designs on Greece or the Aegean. I propose we divide the Mediterranean: Italy takes the western half (Tunis, western Med), Turkey takes the eastern (Greece, Bulgaria). A non-aggression pact between us would allow both powers to expand freely. Are you amenable to such an arrangement?'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, Italy greets you as a fellow Mediterranean power. I propose simple mutual non-aggression: I will not move on Marseilles, and I trust you will not push into Piedmont or Tuscany. My ambitions lie southward toward Tunis and eastward into the Balkans. A friendly Italy on your southern flank frees you to deal with Germany and England. I suggest we formalize this understanding and perhaps coordinate against common threats in the future. Agreed?'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Greetings from Paris. France has no quarrel with Germany in this opening season. I propose we respect each other's natural spheres: France will focus westward and southward (Spain, the Atlantic), while Germany expands east and north. Specifically, I intend to move into Burgundy only as a transit point toward Belgium — I have no designs on Munich. I'd welcome your assurance that A MUN will not enter Burgundy this turn, and in return I'll keep Burgundy clear of any hostile intent toward you. Let us build trust before we consider anything more ambitious."}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, France greets you as a natural partner in the early game. I propose a simple arrangement: France takes Spain and moves into the Atlantic, while England secures Norway and the North Sea. I will move F BRE to MAO this turn — no threat to you whatsoever. I ask only that you keep your fleets out of the English Channel for now, and I'll do the same. A Franco-British understanding keeps Germany honest and gives us both room to grow. Interested?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, let us be frank: France moves toward Spain and the west, you move toward the Balkans and the east. Our interests do not conflict. I will not enter Piedmont — A MAR moves to Spain. In return, I ask that you keep A VEN away from Piedmont as well. A quiet border between us benefits us both while Austria and Turkey fight over the Balkans. Agreed?'}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
