RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Agreed. Our interests align perfectly: F SEV moves to RUM, you take BUL. I will not enter the Black Sea or ARM this spring. In return, keep F ANK out of BLA and away from SEV. Romania is mine, Bulgaria is yours - let Austria worry about both of us pressing from different directions. This arrangement stands as long as you honor it.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, we are in agreement - A WAR will not enter Galicia this spring. I am moving it south toward Ukraine to support my fleet's push into Romania. I expect the same restraint from you regarding Galicia. Let us both grow at the expense of neutrals and Turkey rather than each other. A stable Russo-Austrian border is in both our interests for now."}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I appreciate the pragmatic approach. Norway is yours if you can reach it - I am directing F STP/SC toward Finland or the Gulf of Bothnia rather than contesting Norway directly. My focus is the south. However, I expect you to stay out of the Baltic and away from Swedish waters where my interests lie. We need not clash in the north if we respect these boundaries.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Agreed. Your terms are acceptable - F SEV to RUM, Black Sea and Armenia left untouched by both of us. I will keep F ANK in place this spring and move A CON to Bulgaria. Romania is yours, Bulgaria is mine. This arrangement serves us both well. Let Austria and Italy fight over the scraps while we consolidate. I will hold to this agreement as long as you do.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, we are aligned. Bulgaria and Greece for Turkey, Serbia and Romania for you - this is a clean division. I move A CON to Bulgaria this spring. I ask only that you ensure Serbia is taken promptly so Russia cannot slip in. Together we can contain Russian expansion southward while both growing stronger. I will not threaten your Balkan interests if you respect mine.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your proposal suits me perfectly. Western Mediterranean is yours, eastern is mine - Tunis for you, Greece and Bulgaria for Turkey. I have no fleet moving toward the Ionian this season. Let us both expand freely without interference from each other, and keep an eye on Austria, who sits between us and may grow troublesome if unchecked. Non-aggression confirmed from my side.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Agreed on the spheres of influence. Germany takes Denmark and Holland, England takes Norway and Belgium. My F EDI moves to NTH and F LON to ENG - I will not contest your fleet moving to Denmark. Let us both profit this spring and build a lasting partnership against France and Russia. I expect your fleet stays out of NTH and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I appreciate the goodwill. I accept your proposal - F BRE to MAO is no threat to me, and I will move F LON to ENG without hostile intent toward you. My focus is Norway and the North Sea. However, I must be honest: I intend to contest Belgium, which is a natural English interest. I propose we leave the Channel as a buffer zone between us and both expand outward - you toward Iberia, me toward Scandinavia. Germany is the real threat to watch.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I am moving F EDI to NTH this spring to secure Norway. I ask that you do not move to Norway this turn - let it fall to England, and I will support your interests in Sweden and the Baltic diplomatically. We have no reason to clash in the north. Focus your energies on the south and east where the real prizes lie. A British-Russian understanding in the north benefits us both.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Vienna, I appreciate your response and we are aligned. To be specific about my moves this turn: F NAP moves to ION, A ROM moves to APU, and A VEN moves to TYR. I will NOT touch Trieste. F TRI moving to ADR is welcome - it signals good faith and helps us both in the south. Let us coordinate on the Balkans next season: I see opportunity in Greece and Serbia, and with your forces pushing into Serbia and Romania, we can divide the spoils. A long-term Austro-Italian partnership against Turkey and Russia serves us both well.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Sultan, we are in agreement. I move F NAP to ION this turn, aimed at Tunis - no threat to you in the Aegean. You take Bulgaria, I take Tunis, and we both grow stronger. Austria is the key question between us - I am currently maintaining friendly relations with Vienna, but if they overreach in the Balkans, Italy would be open to coordinating with Turkey against them. For now, let us both expand peacefully and keep communication open. Non-interference is confirmed.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, we are in full agreement. A MAR to Spain, A VEN stays away from Piedmont - our border is quiet. I move south toward Tunis and east toward the Balkans. A peaceful Franco-Italian frontier is in both our interests for years to come. Let us revisit coordination once we have both secured our initial expansions - there may be opportunities against common rivals in the mid-game.'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "England, I'm glad we're aligned. To be concrete: F BRE moves to MAO this turn, A PAR moves to BUR, A MAR moves to SPA. No French unit will touch the Channel or threaten your home waters. I'd ask you confirm F LON stays out of ENG this turn — that keeps the Channel genuinely neutral. If Germany proves aggressive toward either of us, we should coordinate immediately. I see a long partnership here if we both act in good faith now."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I want to be direct with you: A PAR moves to BUR this turn as a transit toward Belgium — I have no hostile intent toward Munich. I'm asking A MUN to stay out of BUR so we don't collide. If you can confirm that, I'll confirm in return that BUR is not a staging ground against you. France's focus is Spain and the Atlantic. Let's not waste our strength on each other when there are easier gains elsewhere for both of us."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, we are agreed — A MAR moves to SPA, not PIE. I will not threaten your northern border. Keep A VEN away from PIE and we have a clean, stable frontier. As you push into the Balkans, know that France will not interfere. I may reach out in future seasons about coordinating pressure on Austria if the opportunity arises — a divided Austria benefits us both. For now, let us simply grow without friction between us.'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, I appreciate your candor. Let us be precise about our moves: I will move F TRI to ADR (not threatening Venice), A BUD to SER, and A VIE to GAL. I ask that you keep A VEN out of TYR and TRI - move it south toward APU or hold. If you move A VEN to TYR, I will interpret that as hostile and respond accordingly. F TRI to ADR actually supports your ION ambitions and keeps us both safe. We have a deal on non-aggression - let's honor it with our actual orders."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, we are in full agreement. Bulgaria is yours, Serbia and Romania are mine. I will move A BUD to SER this spring. I suggest you move A CON to BUL and F ANK to BLA to pressure Russia from the south - this coordinates perfectly with my push into the Balkans. Russia has already told me they want Romania, so we must move fast. A strong Austro-Turkish axis in the Balkans will contain Russia effectively. Let us execute this plan.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I appreciate your message and agree to the Galicia buffer - I will not move into GAL this turn. However, I must be transparent: I intend to move A BUD to SER and F TRI to ADR. Romania is a territory I will need to contest eventually, but not this turn - I am focused on Serbia first. I hope we can maintain peaceful relations while both expanding into our natural spheres. The real threats to both of us are the western powers growing unchecked.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, your proposal aligns well with German interests. I confirm: F KIE moves to Denmark, A BER moves to Kiel, and A MUN moves to Ruhr - I will not contest the North Sea or challenge your fleet movements. Denmark and Holland are my targets this year. France moving into Burgundy concerns me - if they push toward Belgium, that threatens both of us. I suggest you position to take Belgium while I secure Holland, and we present France with a two-front problem if they overreach. This Anglo-German understanding is the foundation of a stable Europe.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your Scandinavian proposal is acceptable. You take Norway via your northern fleet, I take Denmark and Sweden via the Baltic - no competition needed. I confirm A WAR moving south is noted and appreciated; I will keep my armies focused westward this year. Prussia and Silesia will remain quiet from my side. Let us build on this pragmatic foundation - a Russo-German non-aggression arrangement frees us both to expand in our natural directions without wasteful conflict.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I accept your assurance regarding Burgundy. A MUN will move to Ruhr this turn, not Burgundy - you have my word on that. However, I must be clear: Holland is a German interest and I will be moving there. If you intend Belgium, we should coordinate so our moves do not conflict. France expanding west and south, Germany expanding north and east - this division of Europe serves us both. But understand that any French unit that threatens Munich or the Rhineland will be met with force. Keep to your sphere and we have no quarrel.'}]
