INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 1/2
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Friend, I'm moving F ION to TUN this fall to secure Tunis as planned. A VEN will move to TRI - I'd like your blessing or better yet your support for this move. If you support A VEN into TRI, we split the Balkans efficiently: I take TRI, you keep SER and push toward BUD/RUM. Austria controls the land, Italy controls the sea. This is the foundation of a lasting partnership. What are your fall orders?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "As agreed in spring, I'm taking Tunis with F ION this fall. You should be free to take Greece with A BUL - I won't contest it. Our Mediterranean division stands. I propose we maintain this arrangement through 1902 and coordinate against Russia in the Black Sea region - your F BLA is well positioned. Let's keep this partnership strong."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Our borders remain clean and I intend to keep it that way. I'm focused entirely on the eastern Mediterranean this fall - Tunis is my target. No Italian units will threaten Marseilles or Piedmont. I'd welcome a formal non-aggression pact through 1902 so we can both expand freely in our respective directions. What are your plans this fall?"}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'My friend, the time has come to coordinate our autumn moves. I intend to push A BUR into BEL this fall — I need your F ENG to support A BUR - BEL, or at minimum stay out of BEL so I can take it cleanly. In exchange, I will keep F MAO away from your shores and we can discuss dividing the northern neutrals fairly. Germany is the real threat to both of us — let us secure Belgium together and then turn our attention to containing them. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Kaiser, I want to be transparent with you: my A BUR will be moving to Belgium this fall. I have no designs on Munich or any German territory — my ambitions are westward and southward. I propose we formalize a non-aggression pact along the BUR-RUH border. You take Holland, I take Belgium, and we both grow stronger. A Franco-German understanding is the foundation of continental stability. Agreed?'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, our non-aggression holds and I intend to honor it. My moves this fall are directed northwest toward Belgium — I have no interest in Piedmont or your sphere. I would welcome a longer-term understanding: you expand east and south through the Balkans, I expand north and west. We need not compete. Let us keep our border quiet and both prosper.'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Friend, our Balkan arrangement has worked perfectly - I hold Serbia, you hold Bulgaria. Now let's coordinate Fall moves: I intend to hold Serbia and push my fleet toward Greece to support your expansion there. I propose A SER supports your A BUL if you move to GRE, and we split the Balkans cleanly. Russia's fleet in RUM is a threat to both of us - I'd like to discuss how we handle that together. What are your intentions this fall?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Our arrangement held well - I honored the Galicia buffer and moved to Bohemia instead. I'm concerned about your fleet in RUM, which sits adjacent to my Serbian army. I have no hostile intentions toward you, but I need assurance that F RUM will not move against SER or BUD. In return, I'm happy to continue the Galicia buffer and focus my energies westward and southward. Can we agree: F RUM stays in RUM or moves east, and I keep A BOH out of GAL?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I note you held Venice rather than moving to Tyrolia as you suggested - I appreciate that restraint. My fleet in ADR is positioned defensively, not offensively toward you. I propose a formal non-aggression pact: I will not move F ADR into VEN or APU, and you keep A VEN out of TRI and TYR. We both benefit from focusing outward - you toward the Mediterranean, me toward the Balkans. Shall we formalize this arrangement?'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The opening moves went exactly as planned. My fleet is in DEN, army in KIE, army in RUH - perfectly positioned. This fall I intend to move A KIE -> HOL and A RUH supports, securing Holland for Germany. I'll need you to keep F NTH out of HOL - that's our arrangement. In return, I support your position in the North Sea and have no designs on BEL this turn. France is exposed with BUR forward - we should coordinate to squeeze them. What are your intentions for BEL?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Excellent opening for both of us. I'm moving to secure HOL this fall, which keeps me focused westward. I trust your fleet in BOT is heading toward NOR as we discussed - that keeps Scandinavia divided cleanly between us. I'll take SWE next year via the Baltic once I have the builds. No German units are threatening your western flank - PRU and SIL remain quiet. Let's keep this arrangement solid."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "I honored my commitment - MUN went to RUH, not BUR. I expect you noted that. I'm moving to HOL this fall, which is squarely in the German sphere. I have no designs on BEL or BUR this turn. However, I'd caution you that England has two fleets positioned aggressively - NTH and ENG channel. Their army in YOR is also suspicious. You may want to consider whether London's intentions toward the continent are friendly. I'm open to discussing mutual interests."}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Kaiser, the opening moves have gone well for both of us. I have F NTH and F ENG positioned perfectly. My plan this fall: F NTH moves to NOR (securing it for England), F ENG moves to BEL (which I expect you'll support or at least not contest). I'd ask that your F DEN supports my F NTH into NOR if needed, and that A RUH moves to HOL - that's your natural gain this fall. We split the north cleanly: NOR and BEL for England, HOL and DEN for Germany. France has A BUR threatening BEL from the south - if they move there, we both lose. Can you confirm A RUH to HOL and F DEN holds or supports as needed?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I want to be transparent: I moved F LON to ENG as a precautionary measure, not a hostile one. I note your A BUR is positioned near BEL - I intend to take BEL this fall with F ENG. I'd strongly prefer we don't clash over it. If you leave BEL to me, I'll ensure F ENG doesn't threaten any French home centers. BEL is naturally in England's sphere; your strength lies in Iberia and the Mediterranean. Let's avoid a costly Anglo-French war that only benefits Germany. What are your intentions with A BUR?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, glad our spring coordination worked smoothly. I'm moving F NTH to NOR this fall - that's mine as agreed. I trust you're keeping F BOT away from NOR and focused on your eastern ambitions. I'd welcome continued cooperation - England and Russia have no natural conflicts. What are your fall targets? I'm watching Turkey and Austria with interest."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Excellent opening - our agreement worked perfectly. You secured Romania, I secured Bulgaria, and the Black Sea arrangement kept things clean. Now let's coordinate Fall 1901: I intend to move A BUL -> GRE to capture that supply center, and F BLA can hold or support. I'd suggest you consolidate RUM and push toward Scandinavia or Austria as you see fit. I have no designs on SEV or your northern territories - my expansion is southward into Greece and eventually the Aegean. Let's maintain this understanding through 1902."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Good work securing Serbia - that's a solid gain for you. For Fall 1901, I plan to take Greece with A BUL -> GRE, which is squarely in our agreed Turkish sphere. I'd suggest you use F ADR to pressure Italy or move toward Trieste consolidation. One thing worth noting: Russia has F RUM right on your doorstep - you may want to think about how to handle that threat. I'm happy to coordinate pressure on Russia from the south if you're concerned about their Balkan ambitions."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Our eastern/western Mediterranean division is working well. I'm moving A BUL -> GRE this fall to secure my sphere. I notice your F ION is well-positioned - Tunis should be yours for the taking. I'd caution you about Austria's F ADR lurking near your coast - that could be a threat worth watching. If Austria becomes aggressive toward you, I'm open to discussing coordination. For now, let's both expand cleanly in our respective spheres and avoid stepping on each other."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Our arrangement has worked perfectly - I hold RUM, you hold BUL, Black Sea remains yours. Now let's coordinate for Fall 1901. I propose F RUM holds or supports your position, while A SEV moves to ARM to threaten ANK from the north - but only if you want to coordinate a joint push against AUT through the Balkans. Alternatively, if you prefer I keep A SEV in place, I can support your A BUL into SER while A SER is occupied by AUT. What is your preferred direction? I want to ensure we don't step on each other's toes and maximize our combined gains."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, our buffer arrangement in Galicia has held and I appreciate the cooperation. For Fall 1901, I intend to consolidate RUM and keep my forces positioned defensively. I have no designs on BUD or GAL this year. However, I note Turkey is building strength in BUL - a Turkish army in SER would threaten both of us. I suggest we coordinate: if you can hold SER or push toward BUL, I can support from RUM. A strong Austria in the Balkans benefits Russia as much as it does you. What are your Fall intentions?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I'm moving F BOT toward SWE this fall - I'd appreciate you not contesting it. In return, I have no interest in BAL or your northern positions. I'm focused entirely on the south and Balkans. If you're pushing into HOL or BEL this fall, I wish you success - a strong Germany in the west keeps England and France occupied, which suits me perfectly. Let's maintain our non-aggression and both expand in our respective directions."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I accept your non-aggression terms: A VEN stays out of TRI and TYR, and F ADR stays away from VEN and APU. My fall orders are F ION to TUN, A APU holds or supports, A VEN moves to TRI - wait, I'll honor our pact and keep VEN away from TRI. A VEN will move toward PIE or hold. Let's both expand outward and revisit Balkan coordination in 1902 once we've both grown. I value this partnership and will not betray it this season."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, confirmed - F ION moves to TUN this fall, you take GRE with A BUL. Our spheres are clean. I share your concern about Austria's F ADR - I'm watching it carefully. If Austria makes any aggressive move toward my coast, I will want to coordinate with you immediately. For now, let's both secure our gains and build strength. A strong Italy and Turkey together can dominate the Mediterranean and check Russian expansion in the east."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, excellent - our non-aggression pact through 1902 is confirmed. I'm moving entirely east and south this fall, no Italian presence near Marseilles or Piedmont whatsoever. Your northwest expansion and my Mediterranean expansion are perfectly complementary. Let's revisit coordination in 1902 once we've both secured new centers - there may be opportunities to work together against common threats."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Perfect - your move to GRE is exactly what I hoped to hear. I will hold F RUM in place to secure that center, and A SEV will move to ARM to position for future coordination. This keeps us both expanding without conflict. In 1902, I'd like to discuss a joint squeeze on Austria through the Balkans - you from GRE/BUL, me from RUM and GAL. Turkey and Russia together can dominate southeastern Europe. Stay the course and let's both build this winter."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I give you my word: F RUM will not move against SER or BUD this fall. I am consolidating RUM and moving A SEV to ARM - purely to position against Turkey's southern expansion, not toward you. The Galicia buffer holds. However, I urge you to watch Italy carefully - F ADR and A VEN together suggest Italian ambitions in the Adriatic that threaten TRI. A strong Austria is in Russia's interest, and I'd rather see you focused on Italy than worrying about me."}, {'recipients': ['GER', 'ENG'], 'body': "Gentlemen, Scandinavia is yours to divide - NOR to England, SWE to Germany in due course. F BOT is moving to SWE this fall to secure it for Russia's benefit, but I am open to discussing a handoff arrangement with Germany once you have the builds. My focus remains entirely southward. No Russian units threaten your positions - let's all expand in our respective directions and keep this non-aggression solid through 1902."}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Kaiser, we are aligned. My orders this fall: F NTH to NOR, F ENG to BEL. I will NOT move to HOL - that's yours. Please have A KIE move to HOL and A RUH support it. If France tries to take BEL with A BUR, my F ENG will beat them there - but if you could have F DEN support F NTH into NOR, that guarantees Norway for England and frees me to focus on BEL. The Anglo-German partnership is working perfectly. Let's both gain two centers this fall and build from strength."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, I must be direct with you: I cannot support A BUR into BEL - my F ENG is moving to BEL this fall, and that is non-negotiable. BEL is England's natural sphere and I have coordinated with Germany accordingly. However, I have no designs on your home centers or Iberia. If you move A BUR to BEL we will clash and both lose - Germany benefits enormously from Anglo-French conflict. I urge you to redirect A BUR toward Munich or hold it in place. Let England have BEL, keep F MAO away from my shores, and we maintain a workable peace. The alternative is a war that serves only Berlin."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, all proceeds as planned - F NTH to NOR this fall, securing my northern position. I trust you're focused on your southern and eastern ambitions. One thing worth watching: Austria has F ADR and units in SER and BOH - they're well-positioned in the Balkans. Turkey is also expanding. A coordinated Russo-Turkish or Russo-Austrian arrangement could reshape the east significantly. England has no quarrel with Russia and I'd welcome continued coordination. Keep me informed of your intentions."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "I appreciate your cooperative spirit, but I must be direct: A SEV moving to ARM is not acceptable to me - that threatens ANK directly and I will treat it as hostile. Keep A SEV in place or move it north/west. My plan this fall is A BUL -> GRE, F BLA holds. I have no interest in SER or RUM - those are yours and Austria's to contest. Let's maintain our southern/northern division cleanly. If you move SEV to ARM, our understanding is finished and I will act accordingly."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Confirmed: A BUL -> GRE this fall, and I welcome A SER supporting if you wish - though it shouldn't be necessary. Russia's proposal to move A SEV -> ARM is concerning and threatens both of us indirectly. I suggest you consider pressing F RUM with your own forces or at minimum making clear to Russia that Balkan encroachment is unwelcome. I'm watching Russia carefully from the south. Our Balkan division remains solid - Greece is mine, Serbia is yours, and we should coordinate on containing Russian expansion in 1902."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Confirmed on Tunis - take it cleanly. I'm moving A BUL -> GRE as planned. One development worth flagging: Russia is making aggressive noises about moving into ARM which threatens my ANK. If Russia becomes a problem in the east, I may need your F ION to eventually support operations in the Aegean. For now we're aligned - let's both secure our gains this fall and discuss 1902 coordination once we've both built new units."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I must be direct: I will NOT support A VEN into TRI, and I will not allow TRI to fall. TRI is my home center. If you move A VEN to TRI, I will treat it as an act of war and respond accordingly - F ADR will move to block or counter, and I will seek allies against you. However, I genuinely want peace between us. My offer stands: you keep VEN, I keep TRI, we both expand elsewhere. You take Tunis, I take Balkans. If you want a productive partnership, confirm you will NOT move to TRI this fall.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, confirmed: A BUL to GRE is your move, and I will support it - A SER supports A BUL to GRE. This secures Greece for you and keeps our Balkan division clean. On Russia: F RUM is a concern but let's not provoke them yet - I've secured assurances they won't move on BUD or SER this turn. My F ADR will move to ALB to position for future coordination with you. Let's build our alliance carefully and turn on Russia together when the moment is right."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I appreciate your assurances and I will honor our arrangement - A BOH stays out of GAL this fall. My moves this turn: A SER holds or supports Turkish move to GRE (keeping Balkans stable), F ADR moves to ALB (positioning southward, not toward you), A BOH moves to GAL - wait, no, I promised to keep BOH out of GAL, so A BOH moves to VIE or MUN direction. I am focused entirely southward and westward. F RUM staying put is all I ask. Let's maintain this buffer through 1902 and reassess together."}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Confirmed: A RUH moves to HOL this fall, A KIE supports. F DEN will hold in place to secure Denmark. I will not contest BEL - that's yours if you can take it from ENG channel. France has told me they're moving BUR to BEL as well, so you may face a collision there - be aware. Our arrangement stands: HOL for Germany, NOR and BEL for England. Let's both build this winter and discuss next year's coordination against France."}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "I appreciate your transparency. A Franco-German non-aggression along the RUH-BUR border suits me well - I have no interest in BUR this turn. However, I must warn you: England's F ENG is moving to BEL this fall. If your A BUR also moves to BEL, you'll collide and neither of you gets it. You may want to reconsider your move - perhaps BEL next year when you're better positioned, or consider whether England is truly your friend. I take HOL, you take BEL when the moment is right - but not if England beats you there."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Understood on SWE - I have no fleet moving there this fall, F DEN holds in Denmark. SWE is yours to take. Our arrangement remains solid: you expand north and south, I expand west. A strong Russia in the east and a strong Germany in the west is the natural order. Let's both build well this winter and keep our border quiet through 1902."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, I appreciate your candor, but I must be equally direct: A BUR is moving to BEL this fall. I have three units positioned and the momentum to take it. A clash over Belgium benefits only Germany, as you rightly note — so let us avoid it by agreeing now that BEL is mine this turn, and I will actively support your expansion into Scandinavia and the North Sea. F MAO will not threaten your home centers. If you move F ENG into BEL, we will bounce and both lose the center to a future German grab. The smarter play is to let me take BEL now and coordinate against Germany together — I can pressure RUH from BEL while you press from the north. Think strategically, not territorially.'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Kaiser, your warning about England is well-taken — two fleets in the Channel and an army in Yorkshire is an aggressive posture. I am moving A BUR to BEL this fall regardless of English objections. If England contests BEL, I may need German support or at minimum German neutrality. In return, I reaffirm: no French units will move toward Munich, Kiel, or any German center. HOL is yours. Let us build this Franco-German axis into something durable — with Belgium secured, I can help pressure England from the south while you press from the north.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, a formal non-aggression pact through 1902 is agreed — no French units will threaten Marseilles, Piedmont, or any Italian sphere. Good luck in Tunis; that is a smart move. My focus is entirely on Belgium and the northwest this fall. Let us both expand freely and revisit coordination once we have consolidated our gains.'}]
