FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, let us be direct: last autumn we both moved on Belgium and bounced each other, which served neither of us. I am willing to concede Belgium to you this season if you commit to keeping F ENG out of the Channel and away from Brest permanently. In return, I will move A BUR to a non-threatening position — perhaps MUN or RUH to pressure Germany — and we can coordinate against a common target. Germany is growing fast with 5 centers; they are the real threat to both of us. What say you?'}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, France has no designs on Munich or Kiel — my focus remains westward. However, I note England is sitting at 4 centers and has a fleet in the Channel threatening both of us. I propose we coordinate: I push A BUR toward Belgium or hold it as a buffer, while you consider whether England's northern expansion serves your interests. A strong Germany is useful to France as a counterweight to English naval dominance. Let us discuss what arrangement benefits us both in 1902."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, our non-aggression continues to serve us both well. You have Tunis secured — well done. I intend to keep my forces focused northward toward Belgium and away from the Mediterranean. I ask only that you keep A TUS away from Piedmont and the Marseilles approaches. In return, France will not contest your expansion into the Balkans or eastern Mediterranean. We should coordinate to ensure neither England nor Germany grows too dominant in the west.'}]
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Good work last year - we both expanded as planned. This spring I intend to push F NWY toward STP or SWE, and F ENG toward BEL. I need your cooperation: keep F DEN out of NTH and SKA so I have freedom of movement northward. In return, I have no interest in HOL - that's yours to keep. I'd also suggest we coordinate against France: if you can press A HOL toward BEL or threaten BRE from the north, we can squeeze France between us. What are your intentions this season?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, we bounced in BEL last fall - a waste for both of us. I'm willing to discuss a division of interests: England takes BEL, France consolidates Iberia and looks south toward MAR and the Mediterranean. Continued conflict over BEL only benefits Germany. If you move A BUR away from BEL this spring, I'll ensure F ENG does not threaten BRE. Let's stop bleeding each other and focus on real expansion. What do you say?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our arrangement has worked well - you have SWE, I have NWY, no conflict in the north. I intend to press F NWY toward STP this season - I want to be transparent about that. I'm not looking for a fight with you, but STP is a natural target from my position. If you'd prefer to negotiate a different arrangement, I'm open to discussion. What are your plans for the north this year?"}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, our arrangement has served us both well - you secured Norway, I secured Holland and Denmark. Now let us coordinate for 1902. Belgium remains unclaimed and is the obvious next prize. I propose A HOL -> BEL this spring. If you can support from ENG or NTH, we guarantee it. In return, I am happy to see you consolidate the north - I have no designs on Norway or the British Isles. France is the common threat: they sit in BUR with 5 centers already. Let us squeeze them from both sides.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I trust our northern arrangement remains solid. You hold SWE, I hold DEN - no conflict between us there. My attention turns westward toward Belgium and France. I want to assure you that Prussia and Silesia remain quiet on my end - I have no eastern ambitions at this time. If you are pressing south against Turkey or Austria, I wish you success. Let us keep our mutual border peaceful and focus our energies on our respective expansion zones.'}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, I note you hold BUR with an army. I want to be direct: I am moving A HOL -> BEL this spring. I am not moving against you - BEL is neutral and Germany needs it. If you move BUR -> BEL we will collide and neither gains. I propose you move BUR elsewhere - perhaps toward PAR or MAR for defense against England - while I take BEL cleanly. England is your real threat in the west; I can be a useful counterweight if we avoid unnecessary friction between us.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, our cooperation last fall was excellent - your support of A BUL -> GRE was decisive and I won't forget it. Now I need to discuss 1902. I propose: I move A GRE -> BUL (securing that center), F BLA moves to pressure RUM or SEV, and A SMY advances toward ARM. Russia is the common threat - they have 6 centers and are growing fast. I want to coordinate a joint squeeze: you push into RUM from SER while I attack from BLA. If we split RUM and SEV between us, Russia is crippled. What are your intentions this spring? I need to know if you're moving toward RUM so I can support or coordinate."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I must be direct: your move of A SEV -> ARM last fall was a provocation I cannot ignore. ARM threatens ANK directly and I will defend my home centers aggressively. However, I prefer diplomacy to conflict. If you withdraw from ARM this spring and commit to keeping your forces north of the Black Sea, I will hold F BLA in place and not contest RUM. If ARM remains occupied or advances, I will treat this as open war and coordinate with Austria accordingly. Your choice - peace or conflict. I await your response.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, our eastern/western Mediterranean division continues to serve us both well. I'm focused on the Balkans and Black Sea this year - specifically pressuring Russia who is becoming dangerously large with 6 centers. I have no designs on Tunis or the western Med. I'd ask that you keep F TUN positioned to potentially threaten ION or AEG if needed as a distraction for Austria, but otherwise our non-aggression holds firm. Are you planning any moves toward the Balkans I should know about?"}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Friend, our Balkan arrangement has worked beautifully - you hold GRE, I hold SER. Now let's coordinate for 1902. I propose: F ALB moves to GRE to support your position there, while A SER pushes toward BUL or RUM. Turkey should focus on BLA/ANK consolidation and perhaps push into RUM with F BLA while I pressure from SER. Russia is the common threat - F RUM sitting there blocks both of us. If you move F BLA -> RUM and I move A SER -> RUM, we can dislodge the Russian fleet. What are your intentions this spring?"}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, our Galicia buffer has held and I appreciate your restraint. I want to continue our cooperation. This spring I intend to keep A SER in place and move A TYR westward - no threat to you. However, I must be honest: Turkey is eyeing RUM aggressively with F BLA. I suggest we coordinate - if you move F RUM to BUL/EC or SEV, I can support your position in the Balkans against Turkish expansion. Alternatively, if you're willing to cede RUM to me peacefully, I'll guarantee no moves into GAL or UKR and will actively oppose Turkish expansion northward. What do you propose?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I note you now hold TUN and have units in TUS and ROM. I have A TYR positioned and F ALB in the Adriatic region. I want to be direct: I have no interest in VEN or your home centers if you stay out of TRI and TYR. My A TYR will move to VIE or BOH this spring - away from you. In return, keep A TUS away from PIE/VEN approaches to TRI. We should both focus outward - you toward the western Mediterranean, me toward the Balkans. A formal non-aggression pact benefits us both while Germany and France are the real threats to your north.'}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Comrade, our arrangement continues to serve us both well. I intend to push F RUM toward BUL this spring - that neutral center is ripe for the taking and strengthens our combined position against Austria. I propose: F RUM moves to BUL, while your forces consolidate GRE and pressure AUT from the south. I have no designs on CON or ANK - the Black Sea remains your domain. In return, I ask that F BLA supports F RUM into BUL if needed, or at minimum holds to avoid any confusion. Let us coordinate and divide the Balkans cleanly between us.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I want to maintain our cooperative understanding. My forces this spring will focus northward and on consolidating RUM - I have no intention of moving into GAL. However, I must be direct: BUL is an unclaimed center adjacent to my fleet in RUM, and I intend to take it. This does not threaten your core territories. I would suggest we discuss a clear line of division in the Balkans - you hold SER and push toward TRI/VIE consolidation, I take BUL. Turkey is the common threat we should both be watching.'}, {'recipients': ['GER', 'ENG'], 'body': 'Gentlemen, the north remains stable and I intend to keep it that way. F SWE will hold this spring - I have no aggressive intentions toward DEN or NWY. My focus is entirely on the Balkans where BUL is available and Turkey needs watching. I would appreciate continued non-interference in Scandinavia, and in return Russia will not contest your respective spheres in the west and northwest. Let us all grow at the expense of the neutrals rather than each other.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Greetings from Rome. I want to confirm our non-aggression pact remains firm - VEN will not move toward TRI or TYR this season. I'm focused on consolidating my Mediterranean position and have no interest in conflict with Austria at this time. I'd like to discuss potential coordination against Turkey in the Balkans once we're both in stronger positions - their hold on GRE and BUL could be challenged with joint effort. What are your plans for this season?"}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Our Mediterranean division has served us both well - I hold TUN, you hold GRE. I propose we continue this arrangement and look for opportunities to coordinate. Russia's fleet in RUM and their growing strength concerns me - if they push into BUL or the Black Sea region, it threatens both of us. I'm happy to keep our non-aggression pact intact and focus my expansion westward. What are your intentions this season?"}, {'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Our clean border arrangement has worked perfectly. I intend to continue expanding in the Mediterranean and have no designs on MAR or PIE. I'm curious about your plans - Germany looks quite strong with HOL and DEN secured. Have you considered coordinating against them? I can offer diplomatic pressure from the south if you're planning a push toward MUN or BEL."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
