AUT
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'I understand your caution last spring - fair enough. But your proposal gives you BUL AND RUM while I get nothing new. That is not a partnership, that is you using me as a shield. Here is my counter: A GRE moves to BUL (you secure it), F SEV holds or moves east against RUS, and I take GRE with F ALB - one center each. SER remains mine. This is the only equitable arrangement. If you refuse to vacate GRE, I will coordinate with RUS against you instead. The choice is yours - a fair split or a war on two fronts.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I accept your logic about Turkey being the dominant threat. Here is my specific proposal: I move F ALB -> GRE and A SER -> BUL this fall. You move F RUM to support itself or hold, blocking Turkey's F SEV from taking RUM. If Turkey's A GRE moves to BUL, my A SER will bounce it, protecting your flank. We split the Balkans: GRE and BUL for Austria, RUM stays yours. Turkey gets nothing new and faces pressure from both of us. This is the coordinated containment you proposed - do we have a deal?"}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, agreed on coordinating against Turkey. My F ALB moves to GRE this fall to contest Turkish holdings there. If your F ION moves toward AEG or supports my F ALB into GRE, we can crack Turkey's Balkan position together. I will keep A VIE away from your territory entirely - it moves to GAL. A SER pushes toward BUL. The Adriatic remains neutral between us. Let us both profit from Turkish overextension."}]
