ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Excellent work last spring - HOL is now in English hands and Germany is bleeding. France at 6 centers and England at 5, we are the two dominant western powers. Let's finish the job: I intend to move F HOL to KIE this fall while you push A MUN to BER or hold to threaten. If we coordinate, Germany collapses to 2 centers and cannot recover. I'll support your A BUR if needed, or we can split the German carcass - KIE and DEN for me, BER for you. Confirm your intentions so we can synchronize."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I want to be direct with you: England has no interest in your destruction. France is the real threat here - they now hold MUN and are pushing toward BER. I propose we stabilize: I hold F HOL in place and you retake MUN from France. England and Germany together can contain French expansion before it becomes unstoppable. France at 6 centers is dangerous for both of us. What can you offer in return for English restraint toward Germany?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, the situation in the west is evolving rapidly. France has grown to 6 centers and is becoming the dominant continental power - this should concern you as much as it concerns me. I propose we maintain our northern non-aggression understanding: NWY and NTH remain English, SWE and the Baltic remain yours. I have no designs on your northern territories. Let us both focus on containing France's expansion before it threatens everyone."}]
--------------
RUS
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "The situation is clear: Turkey holds SEV illegitimately and must be pushed back. Last turn we both failed to make progress due to poor coordination. This fall I intend to move F RUM to BUL (taking that center) and A UKR to SEV (pressing Turkey's fleet). I need you to stay out of BUL - your forces should focus on GRE and holding SER. If you support my F RUM into BUL or simply stay clear, we both benefit. Turkey is the common enemy here. Confirm you will not contest BUL and we can coordinate properly."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'You hold SEV - my home center - and you expect me to accept this permanently. That will never happen. I am moving on SEV this fall and I will not stop until it is returned. You can choose to negotiate a return of SEV in exchange for a genuine ceasefire and defined spheres, or you can face continued war on multiple fronts as Austria and Italy are both pressing into your Balkan territories. The choice is yours, but my patience is exhausted.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, I see you hold BUD and are positioned in the Aegean. Turkey is our common problem - they have seized my home center SEV and are blocking expansion for both of us. I am pushing F RUM to BUL and A UKR toward SEV this fall. If you can press F AEG toward CON or support pressure on Turkey from the south, we can crack them open together. What are your intentions this turn? I want to coordinate rather than work at cross-purposes.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, the situation has shifted dramatically. I now hold BUD with A BUD and control TRI as a supply center - we need to discuss a new arrangement. I propose: I will move A BUD to VIE (taking Vienna) while you consolidate SER and GAL. Alternatively, if you prefer peace, I will hold A BUD in place and we negotiate a formal division - I keep TRI and BUD, you keep VIE, SER, GAL. Either way, fighting each other only benefits Turkey and Russia. What is your preference? I need an answer this round.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, my F AEG is positioned perfectly. I propose we coordinate against Austria and Russia simultaneously. I can move F AEG to BUL/SC or CON while you push north with F SEV toward RUM. Austria is weakened - A SER and A GAL are isolated while I hold BUD. If you take RUM and I take BUL, we split the Balkans cleanly. I have no interest in your home centers - CON, ANK, SMY are yours. Let's carve up the middle together. Confirm your moves and I'll coordinate accordingly."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I hold A BUD and F AEG - I'm in position to strike deep into Austria or Turkey. I propose we coordinate: I push A BUD toward VIE while you press A UKR toward GAL, squeezing Austria from both sides. Alternatively, if you want to focus on Turkey, I can move F AEG to BUL/SC while you take RUM with F RUM. Austria has F TRI threatening both of us - eliminating them benefits us both. What is your priority this season?"}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, the situation is simple: you hold MUN, my home center, and I intend to take it back. This fall I am moving A KIE -> MUN and A RUH -> MUN with support. You cannot hold against two armies. However, I am a pragmatic man - if you voluntarily withdraw from MUN this turn, I will guarantee your western flank is safe from German pressure and we can discuss a formal partition of influence. England is your real enemy in the west - they hold BEL and threaten your northern coast. I can be your eastern partner if you choose cooperation over futile resistance. Withdraw from MUN and we have a deal. Refuse, and I will take it by force regardless of cost.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, France continues to occupy Munich - my home center. I am committing both A KIE and A RUH to retake MUN this fall. This means HOL will be lightly defended. I ask that you honor our informal understanding and not press into HOL while I deal with France. In return, I will not contest BEL and will actively support Anglo-German coordination against France once MUN is restored. France is the common threat - they hold MUN and BUR simultaneously, threatening both of us. Let us coordinate: you pressure France from BUR/BEL direction, I retake MUN. We can divide French territory between us.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, our northern arrangement continues to serve us both well. I am focused entirely on retaking MUN from France this fall - A KIE and A RUH both move on MUN. F BAL holds in the north. I have no designs on SWE or Scandinavia at this time. Your southern campaign against Turkey appears to be progressing - I wish you success there. Let us maintain our mutual non-aggression and perhaps discuss future coordination once I have stabilized my western front.'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The spring results were frustrating — my A MUN bounced with A KIE, and your F BEL took HOL cleanly. Well played on HOL. Now let's finish Germany off. This fall I intend to push A MUN to BER while you hold HOL and pressure KIE with F HOL. Germany has A KIE, F BAL, and A RUH — they're spread thin. If I take BER and you threaten KIE, Germany collapses to 2 centers and is finished as a power. I'll also move A BUR to support MUN or threaten RUH. F MAO holds for Atlantic security. Confirm you'll hold HOL and support the anti-Germany push — this is the kill shot."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, your position is precarious but not hopeless. I am willing to offer a ceasefire: I hold A MUN in place and do not advance on BER or KIE this fall, if you agree to pull A RUH back to BEL or HOL and cease threatening my position. England is the real danger to both of us — they now hold HOL and BEL and are growing fast. A Franco-German understanding could check English expansion before it's too late. Think carefully: if you fight me, England wins. Respond with your terms."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, Austria is weakened — they lost TRI to you and have only SER, VIE, and GAL. This is the moment to press VIE or push A BUD toward GAL. I have no designs on your Italian centers and am fully occupied with Germany. A coordinated Italian push into Austria while I tie down Germany would benefit us both enormously. What are your plans this fall? I'd like to ensure we're not working at cross-purposes."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, the situation is clear: your F RUM is sitting on a center I intend to take, and your A UKR threatens SEV. We have been fighting over the same territory for two years with neither of us gaining. I propose a practical arrangement: I will move F SEV to RUM this turn - if you move F RUM to BUL or elsewhere, we avoid a costly bounce. In exchange, I will not push further north toward MOS or WAR. You have larger threats from Austria (A GAL) and the western powers. Let us stop bleeding each other and focus on our real enemies. Respond with your intentions.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your F AEG moved to BUL last spring and bounced - you wasted a move. Now you sit in AEG threatening my home centers while I hold GRE, BUL is unoccupied, and Austria is your real rival in the Balkans. I am moving A GRE to BUL this fall. If you move F AEG to CON or SMY, you will find a fight you cannot win alone. But if you move F AEG to ION or EAS and focus on Austria (who holds TRI and threatens your northern centers), we both benefit. Austria has BUD with your army there - coordinate with me against Austria rather than wasting moves fighting me. Specific proposal: you take TRI back, I take BUL and RUM. Non-aggression in the Aegean.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I am moving A GRE to BUL this fall as I have stated. GRE will be vacant - do with it what you will. However, I note that Italy now holds BUD with A BUD and TRI with F TRI - Italy has taken two of your home centers. Your real enemy is Italy, not me. I propose we stop fighting over GRE and instead coordinate: I push into BUL and RUM against Russia, you focus on reclaiming BUD and VIE from Italy. We can divide the Balkans sensibly - Serbia and Romania for Austria, Bulgaria for Turkey. Italy is the common threat. What are your intentions regarding A BUD?'}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, we need to talk plainly. You hold TRI (my home center) and BUD (another of my centers) - this is an existential threat to Austria. I have no interest in prolonged conflict with you when we have common enemies. Here is my proposal: I will not contest VEN or move against your Italian heartland if you return BUD to me this fall (move A BUD out) and we agree on a formal non-aggression line. I can offer you support into GRE or CON if you want to expand against Turkey. My F TRI will move to ADR to give you space. If you refuse, I will be forced to ally with Russia and Turkey against you, and your exposed position in BUD and TRI becomes very vulnerable. What do you say - cooperation or war?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, let us be direct about the situation. Italy has seized BUD and TRI - Austria is being strangled. I propose we coordinate: I move A GAL to BUD to retake it (you support from RUM if possible), and in exchange I will support your move into BUL or wherever you need in the Balkans. Italy is the common threat here - they have 5 centers and are growing fast. A weakened Austria benefits nobody except Italy and Turkey. I can offer you a free hand in RUM and BUL if you help me recover BUD. What specific moves can we coordinate this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, Italy has taken both TRI and BUD from me - they now have 5 centers and a fleet in AEG threatening your position too. I propose we finally coordinate properly: you move A GRE to BUL (securing that center for yourself), I move A SER to support you or contest RUM, and we both pressure Italy's exposed flank. F TRI (my fleet) can move to ADR to threaten Italy from the sea. Italy's F AEG is a direct threat to your CON and SMY - we have aligned interests here. Tell me your specific moves and I will coordinate accordingly. This is the moment to act together."}]
INFO:main:Negotiation sub-round 2/2
--------------
ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "Confirmed - I will move F HOL to KIE this fall to pressure Germany from the north while you push A MUN to BER. Germany is spread thin with A KIE, F BAL, and A RUH - they cannot defend everywhere. If you take BER and I take KIE, Germany is finished. I'll also keep F ENG positioned to support HOL or threaten BRE if needed. Let's execute this cleanly - the German carcass is ours to divide."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, I hear your proposal but I must be honest: France is pushing hard for me to join their kill shot against you, and I am under significant pressure to comply. If you want English restraint, I need something concrete - specifically, acknowledge that HOL is English territory permanently and offer me DEN in exchange for holding F HOL in place this fall. Without a tangible concession, I cannot justify holding back while France takes BER. The clock is ticking - what is your offer?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to flag something important: France now holds 6 centers and is coordinating with multiple powers to eliminate Germany. Once Germany falls, France will be the dominant continental power with 8+ centers - a direct threat to both of us. I am managing this carefully from the west, but you should consider whether a strong France serves your interests. Our northern non-aggression stands firm - NWY and NTH are mine, SWE and Baltic are yours. Let us both watch France carefully.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, your offer is rejected. You occupy Munich - my home center - and expect me to retreat RUH to BEL as a concession? That is not a ceasefire, that is surrender. I am moving A KIE -> MUN and A RUH -> MUN this fall. You cannot hold against two armies without support, and BUR is empty. England is not my concern right now - you are. If you withdraw from MUN voluntarily before orders are locked, I will halt my advance and we can negotiate a genuine partition. If you hold, I take MUN by force and then we discuss nothing - I simply continue west. Your choice.'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, we have a deal. I am committing A KIE -> MUN and A RUH -> MUN this fall to retake my home center. HOL will be undefended - I am trusting you to honor our understanding and leave it alone. In return, I will not contest BEL and will coordinate with you against France once MUN is restored. France at 6 centers threatens us both - they hold MUN, BUR, and have a fleet in MAO threatening your Atlantic position. Once I retake MUN, I propose we divide France: you take BEL and press from the north, I push through BUR toward PAR. Confirm you will hold F HOL in place this turn.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, I want to be transparent with you: my full attention is on France this fall. Both my armies move on MUN. F BAL holds and I have no northern ambitions. I note your fleet in SWE - I have no designs on it and consider our northern arrangement solid. Once I stabilize against France, I would welcome discussion of coordinated pressure on England, who is growing dangerously with 5 centers. Keep your southern campaign strong against Turkey.'}]
--------------
ITA
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I hear your proposal but I cannot simply hand back BUD without guarantees. Here is my final offer: I will move A BUD to VIE this fall - not to hold it permanently, but as a demonstration that I can take your home centers at will. If you want peace, agree now: I keep TRI as my supply center, you keep SER and GAL, and we establish a formal non-aggression line. F TRI must move to ADR immediately as proof of good faith. If you ally with Russia and Turkey against me, I will take VIE and coordinate with France to eliminate you entirely. The choice is yours - a negotiated settlement where Austria survives, or war where Austria does not.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your proposal has merit but your framing is wrong - I am not threatening your home centers, I am positioning for Balkan expansion. Here is my concrete offer: I move F AEG to BUL/SC this fall, you move A GRE to support or hold, and we split the Balkans - BUL goes to me, RUM goes to you via F RUM. I have no interest in CON, ANK, or SMY. Austria is the common enemy - they hold SER and GAL while I hold BUD. If we coordinate now, we can carve up Austria's Balkan position entirely. Confirm you will not contest BUL and I will not move toward your home centers."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, agreed on Turkey as the common problem - but let's be precise about coordination. I will move F AEG to BUL/SC this fall while you push F RUM toward BUL/EC or hold to support. If we both move to BUL we bounce - so I propose I take BUL/SC and you support from RUM, or you move to RUM and I take BUL uncontested. Meanwhile A BUD can move toward VIE or GAL to squeeze Austria. Turkey's F SEV threatens your southern flank - if you can hold RUM and I take BUL, Turkey is boxed in. Confirm your F RUM move so we don't waste both our efforts bouncing each other."}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "Confirmed — let's execute the kill shot on Germany this fall. I will push A MUN to BER while A BUR moves to support MUN or threatens RUH. You take KIE with F HOL and hold DEN. Germany collapses to 1-2 centers and is finished. The split you proposed works perfectly: KIE and DEN for England, BER for France. F MAO holds for Atlantic security. Let's synchronize exactly on this — A MUN -> BER, A BUR supports or threatens RUH, F HOL -> KIE. Germany is done."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, I've considered your offer carefully, but I cannot withdraw from MUN — it is now a French supply center and strategically vital. Your threat to move both A KIE and A RUH to MUN is noted, but if you commit both armies to retaking MUN, you leave BER and KIE exposed to English pressure from HOL. England is already moving F HOL toward KIE — you will lose more than you gain. The pragmatic path is to accept the current line and redirect your forces against England, who holds BEL and HOL and is the true hegemon in the north. I am willing to hold A MUN in place this fall if you hold A RUH and A KIE defensively — a de facto ceasefire while we both watch England."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, Austria has only three centers and is vulnerable — now is the moment to press VIE from BUD or push through TYR. I am fully committed to finishing Germany this fall and cannot assist directly, but a strong Italian push into Austria keeps the eastern board favorable for both of us. Once Germany is neutralized, France and Italy will be the two strongest powers on the continent — let's ensure Austria doesn't recover while we're both occupied elsewhere. Move A BUD toward VIE or GAL and press the advantage."}]
--------------
AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, your offer to 'negotiate' while holding BUD and TRI is not negotiation - it is extortion. I reject your ultimatum entirely. You are overextended: A BUD is isolated deep in Austrian territory, A VEN is exposed, and your fleet in AEG is far from home. I am coordinating with Russia and Turkey against you this very moment. My A GAL moves to BUD to retake it - if you hold A BUD there, it will be surrounded and destroyed. Russia is moving against your exposed flanks. You have one chance: move A BUD to RUM or GAL immediately and we discuss terms. Otherwise Austria, Russia, and Turkey will dismantle your overextended position center by center. The choice is yours."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I accept your proposal - I will not contest BUL this fall. My moves: A GAL to BUD (retaking my home center from Italy's isolated A BUD), A SER holds to secure Serbia, F TRI to ADR to threaten Italy's southern flank. Italy is the primary threat with 5 centers - A BUD is isolated and vulnerable to my A GAL. If you support A GAL into BUD from RUM, we eliminate Italy's forward unit and split their position. After we deal with Italy, we can discuss a proper Balkan division. Confirm you will support A GAL - BUD from RUM this fall."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, agreed - Italy is the primary threat and I accept your Balkan division proposal: Serbia and Romania for Austria, Bulgaria for Turkey. My moves this fall: A GAL to BUD (retaking it from Italy's isolated army), A SER holds SER, F TRI to ADR (threatening Italy's southern position). If you move A GRE to BUL as stated, that secures your position while I focus on recovering BUD. Once Italy is contained, we can formalize the Balkan arrangement. I need you to confirm A GRE is genuinely moving to BUL so I can plan accordingly - and if F SEV can pressure RUM to keep Russia honest, all the better."}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your stubbornness costs us both. My F SEV moves to RUM this fall - if your F RUM has moved to BUL or elsewhere, you lose RUM without a fight. If you stay, we bounce and waste another season. I am not returning SEV - it is mine now. But I offer this: if you move F RUM away from RUM and cease attacks on SEV, I will not push further north. You face Austria in GAL and the western powers are growing - you cannot afford a two-front war with me. Make the rational choice.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your proposal has merit but I will not let you take BUL - that center is mine. Here is the real arrangement: I move A GRE to BUL, F SEV to RUM (supported by A ARM). You move F AEG to ION or EAS and focus on Austria - reclaim ADR, threaten TRI from the sea. Austria is your enemy, not me. CON, ANK, SMY are untouchable - any move toward them ends our cooperation permanently. Confirm you will keep F AEG out of BUL and CON this turn and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, I am moving A GRE to BUL and F SEV to RUM supported by A ARM - this is confirmed. GRE is yours if you can take it. Italy's F AEG will likely contest GRE too, so you may bounce each other there - but that is Italy's problem. Your real move should be A SER supporting my push or contesting RUM from GAL. Italy holds BUD and TRI - five centers to your three. You need to reclaim your homes before Italy runs away with the game. I will not interfere in your fight against Italy if you stay out of BUL and RUM."}]
