[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I hear your situation with Italy - BUD and TRI lost is serious. Here is my concrete proposal for this fall: I move F RUM to BUL (taking that center), A UKR holds or supports. You move A GAL toward BUD to retake it from Italy - I will not interfere with GAL or BUD. Stay completely clear of BUL and RUM. This gives you a path to recover your centers while I secure BUL. Italy is overextended and vulnerable - coordinate your A SER and A GAL against BUD while I press Turkey in the south. Confirm you will not enter BUL and we have a deal.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your proposal to squeeze Austria is interesting but premature - Austria is already weakened and not my primary threat. Turkey holds my home center SEV and that is my focus. Here is what I propose: you move F AEG to BUL/SC to pressure Turkey from the south while I move F RUM to BUL from the north - if we coordinate, one of us takes BUL and Turkey is squeezed. Alternatively, press A BUD toward SER to keep Austria occupied while I handle Turkey. Do not move into RUM or UKR - those are my spheres. What specific move will you make this fall?'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, your offer is rejected. You seized SEV through treachery and now propose I accept your gains while you threaten to take RUM as well - this is not negotiation, it is extortion. I am moving on your positions this fall and I will not stop. Austria and Italy are both pressing into your Balkan centers. You are surrounded on multiple fronts. Return SEV and we can discuss a genuine ceasefire with defined spheres - otherwise you face war on every border until you are eliminated.'}]
