[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, let's be direct. You have A SER and A BUD, I have A VIE and A TYR. We are locked in a mutual stranglehold that benefits neither of us while Turkey and Russia grow stronger. I propose a clean division: I keep VIE and you keep BUD and SER. A TYR moves to BOH (away from you), A VIE holds. In exchange, I need you to leave TRI and the Adriatic to me. Turkey now holds GRE and SEV - they are the real threat to both of us. Let's stop bleeding each other and coordinate against TUR. Respond with your terms."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, my F AEG sits adjacent to GRE, CON, and SMY. I have no desire to attack you if we can reach an understanding. I am willing to move F AEG to ION (away from your centers) if you commit to non-aggression against my positions and share intelligence on Russian movements. I am focused on Austria - BUD and VIE are my targets. What can you offer me in exchange for pulling my fleet back?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, Turkey holds GRE and SEV - they are expanding rapidly and will threaten both of us. My F AEG can pressure CON or GRE while your F RUM threatens BUL. I propose we coordinate: I move F AEG toward CON this spring while you push F RUM into BUL. This splits Turkish attention and opens the Black Sea region. What are your intentions toward Turkey this season? I want to coordinate specific moves.'}]
