RUS
[{'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': "Turkey, your position is untenable. You hold SEV with a fleet while I have F RUM and A UKR pressing you from two directions. Italy's F AEG threatens your Aegean flank, and Austria is rebuilding. I am moving A UKR to SEV and F RUM to BUL this spring - you cannot hold both. Return SEV now and I will halt further aggression and we can discuss a real partition of the Balkans. Refuse, and I will coordinate with Italy and Austria to dismantle your position entirely. This is your last reasonable opportunity."}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, let us coordinate precisely this spring. I am moving F RUM to BUL/EC and A UKR to SEV. If you move F AEG to BUL/SC, we both take BUL simultaneously on different coasts - a clean double capture. Turkey's F SEV is isolated and A ARM cannot reach in time to help. After BUL falls, I propose we jointly press ANK and CON. What are your specific moves this turn? Let us not bounce each other."}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I understand you need BUD back from Italy - that is your priority and I respect it. My priority is BUL and SEV against Turkey. I am moving F RUM to BUL/EC and A UKR to SEV this spring. I will NOT be able to support your GAL-BUD move from RUM as F RUM is moving out. However, if you can retake BUD with your own forces, I will not interfere in the Balkans south of BUL. Let us both focus on our respective enemies - you on Italy, me on Turkey.'}]
--------------
TUR
[{'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': "Austria, the situation is clear: Italy has seized Vienna and Trieste, and is now the dominant threat to both of us. I propose we coordinate directly this spring. I will move A GRE to BUL, securing that center for Turkey. You should focus A SER and A BUD against Italy's overreach - push A BUD toward Vienna to reclaim your home. I can support pressure on Serbia if needed. Russia holds RUM with F RUM, which I intend to contest with F SEV. If you can hold Serbia and push back Italy, we divide the Balkans cleanly: BUL and RUM for Turkey, SER and Vienna for Austria. Italy must be stopped before they reach 7 centers. Confirm your intentions."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, we have been fighting over scraps while Italy quietly accumulated 6 centers including Vienna and Trieste. Italy is now the board leader and threatens us both. I propose a temporary ceasefire: I will not attack RUM this turn if you move F RUM away from the Black Sea region and focus north or west. In return, I hold F SEV defensively. We can both gain more by letting Italy overextend and then striking. I am willing to discuss a formal division - RUM stays Russian, BUL goes Turkish. Think carefully about who the real threat is.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, you now hold 6 centers including Vienna - you are the board leader and every other power will unite against you. I have no interest in being your enemy when Russia and Austria are the more immediate concerns. However, F AEG sitting in my waters is a provocation I cannot ignore. Move F AEG to ION or westward and I will keep my forces out of the Aegean entirely. We can coexist if you respect the eastern Mediterranean as my sphere. If F AEG remains threatening my CON and SMY, I will be forced to act against you regardless of other considerations.'}]
--------------
FRA
[{'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': "The plan worked beautifully last fall — A MUN to BER succeeded, giving France BER while you hold HOL. Germany is now reduced to KIE, DEN, and MUN with three units. Let's finish them this spring. I propose: A BER moves to KIE (or supports your move to KIE), A BUR moves to MUN to take their heartland. You should push F HOL to KIE or support my A BER to KIE. With coordinated pressure, Germany collapses to 1-2 centers this season. Confirm your intended moves so we can synchronize — Germany must not be allowed to recover."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, your position is precarious but not hopeless. I am willing to offer you a ceasefire: I hold A BER in place and A BUR does not advance, in exchange for A KIE and A MUN holding defensively and F BAL withdrawing from the Baltic. This buys you time to negotiate with England and stabilize. The alternative is a coordinated Franco-English assault that eliminates you entirely this year. The choice is yours — cooperation or annihilation. I await your response.'}, {'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, France is consolidating in Germany while you have made impressive gains in Austria. I propose we coordinate: you press Austria into BUD and SER while I handle Germany. Neither of us should allow Russia to grow unchecked — they sit at 6 centers and are the emerging threat. Are you willing to discuss a joint approach to contain Russian expansion while we each consolidate our current gains? I see a natural division: France dominates the north and west, Italy the south and center.'}]
--------------
GER
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': 'France, let us be direct: you hold BER, my home center, and I hold MUN with A MUN. This situation is untenable for both of us. I propose an immediate exchange - you withdraw A BER to SIL or PRU, I acknowledge your western gains and turn my attention elsewhere. If you refuse, I will spend every resource I have making your position in Germany untenable. I have A KIE, A MUN, and F BAL - I can make BER very uncomfortable for you. A negotiated settlement serves us both better than a grinding war that weakens us while England and Italy grow fat. What do you say?'}, {'recipients': ['ENG'], 'body': 'England, France now holds BER and 6 supply centers - they are the dominant western power and a direct threat to both of us. I propose we coordinate against France this season: I will move A MUN -> BUR and A KIE -> BER to retake my home center, while you press F HOL -> BEL or threaten France from the north. France cannot defend BER, MUN, and BUR simultaneously. This is the moment to cut them down before they reach 7-8 centers. I am offering you BEL in exchange for your active support against France. What specific moves can you commit to?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, Germany is in a difficult position with France occupying BER, but I am fighting back. I want to assure you our northern arrangement remains intact - I have no designs on SWE or your Scandinavian position. My focus is entirely westward against France. I would ask only that you keep your units away from PRU and SIL while I deal with this French aggression. In return, I will support your southern campaign diplomatically and stay out of your way in the east. Are we agreed?'}]
