AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, you hold VIE and TRI - both Austrian home centers - while I'm reduced to two units. This is unacceptable and I will dedicate every resource to your destruction. Russia, Turkey, and Germany all have reason to fear your 6-center position. I am actively coordinating a coalition against you. Your only path to avoiding this is to return VIE immediately and withdraw A TYR. Otherwise, expect coordinated attacks from multiple directions this season."}, {'recipients': ['RUS', 'TUR'], 'body': "Italy now holds 6 centers including both VIE and TRI - they are the runaway leader and must be stopped. I propose we coordinate: I will move A SER - BUL (taking the unowned center), and I need your assurance that neither of you contests BUL this turn. In return, I will support either of you against Italy's exposed flanks. Russia, your F RUM could pressure BUL/EC or support moves against Italy. Turkey, your A GRE could move to BUL or support my move there. Let's agree: BUL goes to Austria, and we jointly pressure Italy. What specific moves can you commit to?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, France has taken BER and holds 6 centers - they are a serious threat to you. Meanwhile Italy has 6 centers and occupies my home territory. I propose we both focus on our respective threats: I will handle Italy in the south if you can pressure France. Specifically, can you move A MUN toward BUR or hold to contain France? I'm moving A SER - BUL this turn to expand, and A BUD will position to eventually threaten Italy's northern flank. A coordinated effort between us benefits both powers."}]
