ENG
[{'recipients': ['FRA'], 'body': "France, our partnership has served us both well - you hold BER, I hold HOL. Now let's finish Germany: I'll move F HOL to KIE (undefended) and F NTH to DEN, while you press A BER toward KIE or hold to consolidate. With Germany eliminated, we can divide their remaining centers cleanly. I propose KIE and DEN go to England, MUN stays French. Agreed?"}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': 'Germany, France has taken BER and threatens your existence. I have no interest in seeing France dominate the continent - a strong Germany serves as a useful counterweight. I propose a temporary arrangement: I will hold F HOL in place and not press KIE if you commit A KIE to support A MUN against French pressure. Your survival depends on checking France now, and I can help by keeping my fleets defensive. What can you offer me in return for this restraint?'}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, France now holds 6 centers and is the dominant continental power - this threatens us both. I'm positioned in the North Sea and Holland; you have Sweden and Norway adjacent. I propose we coordinate: I'll focus pressure on France's northern flank while you maintain your position. Let's establish a firm non-aggression understanding on NWY and SWE - those stay as they are - and focus our energies on the real threats. Are you open to a formal arrangement?"}]
