TUR
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': "Italy, we have a deal. Move F AEG to ION this turn and I will keep all Turkish forces out of the Aegean. My moves this spring: A GRE to BUL, F SEV holds or contests RUM, A ARM supports defensively. I will share what I know - Russia is moving A UKR toward SEV and F RUM toward BUL, so your F AEG moving to ION is safe and positions you well against Austria's southern flank. Non-aggression between us is in both our interests while Russia and Austria remain active threats."}, {'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': 'Russia, your ultimatum is noted but miscalculated. You claim to coordinate Italy and Austria against me - but Italy is moving F AEG to ION and focusing on Austria, not me. Austria is too weak to threaten SEV. Your A UKR to SEV and F RUM to BUL will both fail: F SEV is supported by A ARM, and BUL will be contested by my A GRE. You are overextended with 6 centers spread thin. I am offering you a genuine partition: keep RUM, I take BUL. F SEV stays in SEV, we establish a stable border. Reject this and we both waste moves while Italy reaches 8 centers unopposed.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I cannot give you BUL - that center is critical to my expansion and I have been contesting it for two years. My A GRE moves to BUL this turn. However, I support your push against Italy completely: A BUD should retake VIE, A SER holds or supports. I will not interfere with SER or your Austrian home centers. Focus entirely on Italy - they are at 6 centers and must be stopped. Once Italy is contained, we can discuss a clean Balkan division with SER and RUM for Austria, BUL for Turkey. This is the only arrangement that stops Italy from winning.'}]
