AUT
[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, your proposal is rejected. You hold VIE and TRI - two of my three home centers - and offer me nothing but what I already have. I will not legitimize your theft. My moves this turn: A BUD threatens VIE, A SER holds Serbia. Russia is moving F RUM out of the Balkans, Turkey is moving A GRE to BUL - your southern flank is exposed. Return VIE now and withdraw A TYR to BOH, or I will spend every remaining turn ensuring your elimination even at cost to myself. This is your final warning.'}, {'recipients': ['RUS', 'TUR'], 'body': "Russia, Turkey - I hear you both clearly. My moves this turn: A BUD - VIE (retaking my home center from Italy), A SER - BUL (claiming the unowned center). Russia, your F RUM moving to BUL/EC will bounce my A SER - I ask you instead to move F RUM to SEV or hold, letting me take BUL uncontested. Turkey, if A GRE moves to BUL as you say, we bounce each other and Italy benefits. I propose: Turkey takes GRE (hold it), I take BUL with A SER, Russia focuses on SEV. Italy at 6 centers is the existential threat - let's not fight over BUL while they consolidate. Confirm F RUM stays out of BUL."}, {'recipients': ['GER'], 'body': "Germany, France holds BER and 6 centers - they are your primary threat and mine is Italy. My moves: A BUD - VIE, A SER - BUL. I need you to hold A MUN defensively against France and consider A KIE toward DEN or pressure on France's eastern flank. If France takes MUN again you are finished. I will handle Italy in the south. A coordinated Germany-Austria front against France and Italy respectively is our best path to survival against these two 6-center powers."}]
