[{'recipients': ['RUS'], 'body': "Russia, I am moving F AEG to CON this spring - not BUL/SC. Turkey's capital is the real prize and I can threaten it directly while you take BUL with F RUM. This splits Turkish forces completely. My A VIE holds to secure Vienna, A TYR moves to BOH to pressure Germany. Confirm you are moving F RUM to BUL and A UKR to SEV - if Turkey's F SEV is taken and CON threatened simultaneously, Turkey collapses. Let's execute this precisely."}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, I hear your concerns and I am willing to make a concrete gesture: F AEG moves to ION this spring, away from CON and SMY. In return, I need you to stay out of the Aegean and keep A GRE where it is. Austria is threatening to build a coalition against me and I cannot fight on two fronts - I need the eastern flank quiet. If you attack me now, Russia wins. We both lose. Keep the peace this season and we can discuss a formal division of the Balkans next fall.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, your coalition threats are empty - Russia is moving against Turkey, not me, and Turkey wants non-aggression with Italy. You have two units against my three in the region. I am offering you a final settlement: I keep VIE, you keep BUD and SER, and we both turn against Turkey together. A TYR moves to BOH this spring as a gesture of good faith - away from your territory. If you reject this and attack, I will take BUD with A VIE supported by A TYR and you will be eliminated within two seasons. Choose cooperation or elimination.'}]
