[{'recipients': ['ITA'], 'body': 'Italy, my moves are confirmed: F RUM - BUL/EC and A UKR - SEV. If you move F AEG to BUL/SC we both take BUL on different coasts simultaneously - this is clean and profitable for both of us. Turkey cannot stop both moves. After this turn, I propose we press CON and ANK together. Do not let Austria take BUL - they asked me to cede it to them and I refused. BUL belongs to whoever takes it first, and we should take it together.'}, {'recipients': ['TUR'], 'body': 'Turkey, your ceasefire offer is too little too late. You seized SEV treacherously and have refused every reasonable settlement. Italy holds 6 centers and is indeed a threat, but you are the immediate threat to my home territory. Return SEV and I will consider redirecting against Italy - that is the only deal on the table. Otherwise my moves stand: A UKR to SEV, F RUM to BUL. You cannot hold both with one fleet.'}, {'recipients': ['AUT'], 'body': 'Austria, I cannot cede BUL to you - I need it to pressure Turkey who holds my home center SEV. My moves are F RUM to BUL/EC and A UKR to SEV. Italy is indeed the board leader and I agree they must be checked, but my immediate crisis is Turkey. Focus your forces on retaking VIE and BUD from Italy - that is where your energy belongs. Once Turkey is contained, we can discuss coordinating against Italy together.'}]
